    "faq": {
      "type": "lsc-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_1": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Why should I choose a medical doctor for anti-wrinkle injections?",
            "answer": "<p>Anti-wrinkle injections are prescription-only medicines that require medical assessment before treatment. A doctor has advanced training in facial anatomy, safe prescribing, and complication management. At Laser Skin Clinics, all treatments are performed by an NHS Consultant Physician, ensuring precision, safety, and appropriate dosing tailored to your muscle structure.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_2": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How do Anti Wrinkle injections work?",
            "answer": "<p>Anti-wrinkle injections temporarily relax specific facial muscles responsible for dynamic expression lines. By reducing repetitive muscle contraction, lines such as frown lines, forehead lines, and crow’s feet soften while natural facial movement is preserved.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_3": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How long do results typically last?",
            "answer": "<p>Results usually last between 3–4 months, depending on your muscle strength, metabolism, and lifestyle factors. With consistent treatment, many patients find results may last slightly longer over time.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_4": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "When will I see results?",
            "answer": "<p>You may begin to notice softening within 3–7 days. Full results are typically visible at around 14 days, which is why a two-week clinical review is included.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_5": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Will my results look natural?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. Our approach focuses on subtle softening while maintaining natural facial expression. We use minimum effective dosing and precise placement to avoid a “frozen” or overdone appearance.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_6": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Does the treatment work?",
            "answer": "<p>Most patients describe the treatment as mildly uncomfortable rather than painful. The injections use very fine needles and are completed quickly. Discomfort is brief and generally well tolerated.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_7": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is there any downtime?",
            "answer": "<p>There is minimal downtime. You may experience mild redness, small bumps at the injection sites, or slight bruising, which typically resolves within a few hours to a few days. Most patients return to normal activities immediately.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_8": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What happens at the two-week review?",
            "answer": "<p>At your two-week review, results are assessed once the treatment has fully developed. If minor adjustments are clinically appropriate, these can be discussed and addressed to ensure balanced, natural outcomes.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_9": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Are anti-wrinkle injections safe?",
            "answer": "<p>When prescribed and administered by a qualified medical professional, anti-wrinkle injections have an established safety profile. As with any medical procedure, potential risks and side effects will be discussed during consultation before treatment proceeds.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_10": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Who may not be suitable for anti-wrinkle injections?",
            "answer": "<p>Treatment may not be suitable if you are pregnant or breastfeeding, have certain neuromuscular conditions, active infection at the treatment site, or known allergy to botulinum toxin. Suitability is always confirmed during medical consultation.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_11": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can I have treatment on the same day as my consultation?",
            "answer": "<p>If medically appropriate and following full assessment and prescription, treatment can often be performed on the same day. Suitability is always confirmed during consultation.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_12": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What are possible side effects?",
            "answer": "<p>Temporary side effects may include mild swelling, redness, bruising, or headache. Rare complications will be discussed during consultation. Choosing a medically qualified injector significantly reduces risk.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_13": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Who performs the injections?",
            "answer": "<p>All cosmetic injections at Laser Skin Clinics are carried out personally by Dr Scotton (MBBS, MRCP (UK), BSc, MSc).<br/><br/>She is an appointed NHS Consultant with more than 12 years of medical experience and additional aesthetic training through the Royal Society of Medicine.<br/><br/>Her extensive background ensures your treatment is delivered safely and to the highest professional standard.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_14": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is your cancellation policy?",
            "answer": "<p>Cancellations up to 24 hours before your appointment will receive a full refund or can be rescheduled.<br/><br/>Any cancellations on the day can be rescheduled but will not be refunded.<br/><br/>If you do not show to your appointment you will not receive a refund or a reschedule. Please note that we offer email and text appointment reminders right up until 24 hours before your appointment.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_15": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "I would like to speak to someone before I book my treatment, how is best to do this?",
            "answer": "<p>If you would like to speak to someone please do one of the below.<br/><br/>- Use the enquiry button.<br/><br/>- Contact us via email at info@laserskinclinics.co.uk<br/><br/>- Call us during opening hours on 01902 256667<br/><br/>- Send us a WhatsApp by clicking the WhatsApp button on the website.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_16": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What can cosmetic injections treat?",
            "answer": "<p>Cosmetic injections can be used to reduce fine lines and wrinkles, restore facial volume, reshape lips, and soften dynamic expression lines.<br/><br/>They can also be used for medical indications such as migraine management and excessive sweating (hyperhidrosis).</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_17": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is there any downtime?",
            "answer": "<p>Downtime is minimal.<br/><br/>You may have slight redness or swelling immediately after treatment, but this normally settles within a few hours.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_18": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What product do we use when administrating anti wrinkle injections?",
            "answer": "<p>We only use botox</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_19": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How long do results last?",
            "answer": "<p>Results vary depending on the product used and individual response.<br/><br/>Anti-wrinkle injections generally last around 3 to 4 months, while dermal fillers can last between 6 and 12 months.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_20": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Are cosmetic injections safe?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes, when performed by an experienced medical professional.<br/><br/>At Laser Skin Clinics, all products are FDA-approved and treatments are administered by Dr Scotton in a sterile, clinical environment.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
